-- Ireland Beats Defending Champ Wales 30-22 in Six Nations Rugby
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-02-02T15:48:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-02/ireland-beats-defending-champ-wales-30-22-in-six-nations-rugby.html
Ireland held on to defeat defending
champion Wales 30-22 in the opening game of rugby union’s Six
Nations Championship  Tries from Simon Zebo, Cian Healy and  Brian O’Driscoll 
helped Ireland to a 30-3 lead early in the second half at
Millennium Stadium in Cardiff. Alex Cuthbert, Leigh Halfpenny and
Craig Mitchell then touched down as Wales rallied before falling
short.  Jonathan Sexton  kicked three penalties and three
conversions to finish with 15 points for the Iriah, while
Halfpenny added a penalty and two conversions to his try.  England plays Scotland in today’s second game at Twickenham
Stadium in London.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  